<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: CPU Reset Noob question]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11187&amp;p=128028#p128028"><![CDATA[
/RESET consumes as many clocks as it is low, probably at least several thousand for a practical power-on reset circuit, plus about seven after it rises. These seven are visible only with respect to other hardware that may take more or less time to respond to a rising edge on /RESET.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed Apr 23, 2014 6:30 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
